      "widgets_values": [
        "QUICK PANEL · Z-IMAGE TURBO\n\nMODELS:  #1 diffusion_models/z_image_turbo_bf16.safetensors  |  #23 text_encoders/qwen_3_4b.safetensors (CLIPLoader type: qwen_image)  |  #24 vae/ae.safetensors\n\nANTI-FLICKER:  fixed seed · euler + turbo scheduler · CFG 1.0 · 8 steps flat · eased strength/noise · slow zoom\n\nCONTINUATION — three steps:\n  1. Unmute #28 (WAS_Image_Save). Set its output_path to your ComfyUI input/ directory (e.g. /home/user/ComfyUI/input). Leave filename_prefix as z_image_turbo_continue, overwrite_mode prefix_as_filename.\n  2. Queue a run. The last frame is saved to input/z_image_turbo_continue.png automatically.\n  3. Set use_init = Yes in #8 to continue from that frame. Toggle back to No for a fresh start.\n  NOTE: without WAS Node Suite installed, right-click the #20 preview → save manually → drop in input/z_image_turbo_continue.png.\n\nALTERNATIVE ANIM NODES (disabled, in row below):  #25 Depth Warp (3D mode) · #26 Diffusion Cadence (smoother inter-frame motion) · #27 Color Coherence (stable colours). Right-click → enable to activate.\n\nCONTROLNET (muted, bottom-right):  #29 ControlNetLoader + #30 DeforumControlNetApply. Unmute and wire: CLIPTextEncode → #30 conditioning input · control image → #30 image input. ⚠️ DeforumSingleSampleNode (#9) builds its own conditioning internally — ControlNet output must feed a DeforumKSampler/iterator-based path, not #9 directly."
